Participants acknowledged that technology has proven a vital resource, as work-from-home plans and other strategies put in place to contain the spread of virus disrupted more traditional models of product and service delivery. The global Covid-19 pandemic has resulted in changes in advertising, marketing, promotions and media spend, forcing businesses and brands to re-evaluate their thinking about current and future advertising and marketing campaigns to maintain a steady stream of income. 

Most companies with trusted brands managed to leverage technology during the pandemic to remain afloat in the past nine months during Covid-19 peak in Africa. 



